01:10:13.660 --> 01:10:16.790
is trying to essentially
knock out your cortex.

01:10:16.790 --> 01:10:20.070
It's sedating your cortex,

01:10:20.070 --> 01:10:22.190
and sedation is not sleep.

01:10:22.190 --> 01:10:24.150
But when we have a couple
of drinks in the evening,

01:10:24.150 --> 01:10:25.780
when we have a couple of nightcaps,

01:10:25.780 --> 01:10:28.080
we mistake sedation for sleep

01:10:28.080 --> 01:10:31.140
saying, well, I always when
I have a couple of whiskies

01:10:31.140 --> 01:10:32.490
or a couple of cocktails,

01:10:32.490 --> 01:10:35.260
it always helps me fall asleep faster.

01:10:35.260 --> 01:10:36.690
In truth, what's happening is that

01:10:36.690 --> 01:10:38.940
you're losing consciousness quicker,

01:10:38.940 --> 01:10:41.400
but you're not necessarily falling

01:10:41.400 --> 01:10:44.110
naturalistically asleep any quicker.

01:10:44.110 --> 01:10:46.370
So that's one of the first sort of things

01:10:46.370 --> 01:10:47.790
just to keep in mind.

01:10:47.790 --> 01:10:49.280
The second thing with alcohol

01:10:49.280 --> 01:10:51.190
is that it fragments your sleep.

01:10:51.190 --> 01:10:52.990
And we spoke about the
quality of your sleep

01:10:52.990 --> 01:10:56.400
being just as important as the quantity.

01:10:56.400 --> 01:10:59.110
And alcohol through a
variety of mechanisms,

01:10:59.110 --> 01:11:01.380
some of which are activation

01:11:01.380 --> 01:11:03.190
of that autonomic nervous system,

01:11:03.190 --> 01:11:05.690
that fight or flight branch
of the nervous system.

01:11:06.560 --> 01:11:09.180
Alcohol will actually have you waking up

01:11:09.180 --> 01:11:11.260
many more times throughout the night.

01:11:11.260 --> 01:11:14.390
So your sleep is far less continuous.

01:11:14.390 --> 01:11:16.040
Now, some of those awakenings

01:11:16.040 --> 01:11:19.060
will be of conscious
recollection the next day,

01:11:19.060 --> 01:11:20.710
you'll just remember waking up,

01:11:20.710 --> 01:11:22.690
many of them won't be.

01:11:22.690 --> 01:11:25.810
And so but yet, your
sleep will be littered

01:11:25.810 --> 01:11:28.750
with these sort of punctured awakenings

01:11:28.750 --> 01:11:29.800
throughout the night.

01:11:30.937 --> 01:11:31.950
And again, when you wake
up the next morning,

01:11:31.950 --> 01:11:35.250
you don't feel restored
by your sleep, you know,

01:11:35.250 --> 01:11:38.120
fragmented sleep or non continuous sleep

01:11:38.120 --> 01:11:40.500
in this alcohol induced way,

01:11:40.500 --> 01:11:42.540
is usually not good quality sleep,

01:11:42.540 --> 01:11:44.403
but you feel great on the next day.

01:11:45.810 --> 01:11:49.030
The third part of alcohol
in terms of an equation

01:11:49.030 --> 01:11:52.070
is that it's quite potent
at blocking your REM sleep,

01:11:52.070 --> 01:11:54.010
your rapid eye movement sleep.

01:11:54.010 --> 01:11:55.540
And REM sleep is critical

01:11:55.540 --> 01:11:57.950
for a variety of cognitive functions.

01:11:57.950 --> 01:11:59.830
Some aspects of learning and memory

01:11:59.830 --> 01:12:00.980
it seems to be critical

01:12:01.820 --> 01:12:03.230
for aspects of emotional
and mental health.

