01:15:21.470 --> 01:15:23.760
but across the different stages,

01:15:23.760 --> 01:15:26.470
but what we also know is that
when you disrupt REM sleep,

01:15:26.470 --> 01:15:29.340
there are those growth
hormone consequences.

01:15:29.340 --> 01:15:32.110
So it's not an exclusive system

01:15:32.110 --> 01:15:33.870
just like with testosterone,

01:15:33.870 --> 01:15:36.530
we can see changes
throughout non REM sleep,

01:15:36.530 --> 01:15:39.640
but if you ask when are
the peak release rates

01:15:39.640 --> 01:15:42.770
of testosterone, it's right
before we go into REM sleep,

01:15:42.770 --> 01:15:44.380
and then during REM sleep.

01:15:44.380 --> 01:15:46.550
- And of course,
testosterone being important,

01:15:46.550 --> 01:15:48.336
both for males and females.

01:15:48.336 --> 01:15:49.662
- For men and women, yeah.

01:15:49.662 --> 01:15:51.520
- Right, for libido and
tissue repair and well being.

01:15:51.520 --> 01:15:54.920
Nobody, regardless of
chromosomal, hormonal,

01:15:54.920 --> 01:15:56.410
or any other background

01:15:56.410 --> 01:15:58.600
wants to have their normal levels

01:15:58.600 --> 01:16:00.930
of testosterone reduced acutely,

01:16:00.930 --> 01:16:01.970
that's just a bad

01:16:01.970 --> 01:16:04.010
it equates to a terrible set

01:16:04.010 --> 01:16:05.750
of psychological and physical symptoms.

01:16:05.750 --> 01:16:07.140
- Yeah, and the mortality risk

01:16:07.140 --> 01:16:09.190
that's associated with low testosterone

01:16:09.190 --> 01:16:10.720
is non trivial.
- Prostate cancer.

01:16:10.720 --> 01:16:12.020
- Right, exactly, you know.

