01:16:26.760 --> 01:16:29.730
What we've discovered
over the past 20 years

01:16:29.730 --> 01:16:30.680
here at The Sleep Center,

01:16:30.680 --> 01:16:34.710
is that there is no major
psychiatric disorder

01:16:34.710 --> 01:16:38.450
that we can find in which sleep is normal.

01:16:38.450 --> 01:16:40.270
And so I think that firstly told us

01:16:40.270 --> 01:16:42.170
there is a very intimate association

01:16:42.170 --> 01:16:45.723
between your emotional mental
health and your sleep health.

01:16:46.730 --> 01:16:49.990
But when it also comes to REM sleep,

01:16:49.990 --> 01:16:52.630
I think what's fascinating is that

01:16:52.630 --> 01:16:54.600
it's not just about your emotional health,

01:16:54.600 --> 01:16:57.600
it's not just about your hormonal health

01:16:57.600 --> 01:17:01.810
we've also been seeing other
aspects of you know, cognition.

01:17:01.810 --> 01:17:03.980
But then there was a report,

01:17:03.980 --> 01:17:06.870
I think it could have
been about two years ago,

01:17:06.870 --> 01:17:10.483
out of Harvard, I think it
was Beth Clements group.

01:17:11.450 --> 01:17:13.440
They found that,

01:17:13.440 --> 01:17:16.670
